      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
      "body" : "-1: That is actually a <b>really bad</b> technique to create a directory. The access to the FS is not reserved to a dedicated resource. Between <code>if(!theDir.exists())</code> and <code>theDir.mkdir()</code> the status could have changed, as well as it could change in between <b>not</b> creating the directory (because of <code>exists</code> returning <code>true</code>) and needing it. The result of the method <code>exists</code> should never be used to decide wether to create a directory or not. Just call <code>mkdir</code>, no exception will be thrown if it already exists."
